---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Contact — Sven Read"
  description="Get in touch with Sven Read — Senior Product Designer based near Munich, working remotely on complex B2B systems and AI-first products."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 md:px-10 pt-32 md:pt-40 lg:pt-48 pb-32">
    <p class="font-sans text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-accent mb-6">
      Contact
    </p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl leading-[1.05] tracking-tight">
      Get in touch.
    </h1>
    <p class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl text-muted mt-8 leading-snug">
      Always down to talk about <strong>complex B2B systems</strong>, the design–engineering bridge, and AI-first product work. The most rewarding conversations start with something specific.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-16 md:mt-20 border-t border-hairline pt-12 md:pt-16">
      <p class="font-sans text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-muted mb-6">
        Primary
      </p>
      <a
        href="mailto:me@svenread.com"
        class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl tracking-tight text-ink hover:text-accent transition-colors inline-block"
      >
        me@svenread.com
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 md:mt-20 border-t border-hairline pt-12 md:pt-16">
      <p class="font-sans text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-muted mb-6">
        What I'm looking for
      </p>
      <p class="font-sans text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <strong>Senior, staff, or principal IC roles</strong> on small-to-mid teams building complex software — surgical, infrastructure, industrial, fintech, or AI-first. Remote preferred; hybrid possible for the Munich area. No people-management track. Bilingual roles welcome — German and English are both native.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 md:mt-20 border-t border-hairline pt-12 md:pt-16">
      <p class="font-sans text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-muted mb-8">
        Elsewhere
      </p>
      <ul class="flex flex-col">
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/svenread/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="group flex items-center justify-between gap-4 py-6 md:py-8 border-b border-hairline hover:border-accent transition-colors"
          >
            <span class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">LinkedIn</span>
            <span class="font-sans text-sm text-muted">linkedin.com/in/svenread ↗</span>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/starburst1977"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="group flex items-center justify-between gap-4 py-6 md:py-8 border-b border-hairline hover:border-accent transition-colors"
          >
            <span class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">GitHub</span>
            <span class="font-sans text-sm text-muted">github.com/starburst1977 ↗</span>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://dribbble.com/starburst1977"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="group flex items-center justify-between gap-4 py-6 md:py-8 border-b border-hairline hover:border-accent transition-colors"
          >
            <span class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">Dribbble</span>
            <span class="font-sans text-sm text-muted">dribbble.com/starburst1977 ↗</span>
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 md:mt-20 border-t border-hairline pt-12 md:pt-16">
      <p class="font-sans text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-muted mb-6">
        Before you write
      </p>
      <p class="font-sans text-base text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
        A few things that help me reply quickly and well.
      </p>
      <ul class="flex flex-col gap-3 font-sans text-base text-muted leading-relaxed">
        <li class="pl-6 relative before:content-['—'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-accent">
          <strong>Recruiters:</strong> company name (or anonymized but specific industry), role title, comp range, and on-site/remote split. If those aren't shared yet, just say so — but vague outreach without any of these tends to get archived.
        </li>
        <li class="pl-6 relative before:content-['—'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-accent">
          <strong>Hiring managers:</strong> what the team is building, who I'd work with, and what the design org looks like today.
        </li>
        <li class="pl-6 relative before:content-['—'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-accent">
          <strong>Freelance or contract:</strong> scope, rough timeline, and which language (German or English) the engagement runs in.
        </li>
        <li class="pl-6 relative before:content-['—'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-accent">
          I'm based in <strong>CET</strong> (Munich) and reply during European working hours. Inbound from US timezones still gets answered — just maybe not within the hour.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
